        "description": "This project details how to build a low-cost, portable, battery-powered incubator for on-site bacterial analysis of water samples using Petrifilm plates. This device is designed to be used in developing world scenarios where access to constant electrical power or expensive commercial incubators is limited.",
        "steps": [
            "Assemble the required materials, referring to the Bill of Materials PDF for online sources and prices.",
            "Cut the foam insulation into the appropriate patterns using the provided templates: one bottom, one top, and nine middle layers. Adjust the number of middle layers to fully insulate the cooler, and closed-cell foam with a high R-value is recommended.",
            "Cut the cardboard components using the templates, including a Petrifilm holder with a creased shelf and a heating pad spacer with slits and a divot for the thermocouple.",
            "Drill a thermometer hole in the inner chamber, using a 5/32\u201d drill bit, then widen the hole to 3/8\". The hole should allow the thermometer to extend to the inner chamber.",
            "Assemble the electrical heating system according to the wiring diagram, connecting the thermostat, heating pads, terminal block, fuse, and battery.",
            "Assemble the heating pad holder by sliding the heating pads into the cardboard spacer, securing them with hot glue, and gluing the thermocouple to the back. Then, slide the assembly into the inner chamber.",
            "Mount the thermometer in the incubator by sliding it through the hole and securing it with hot glue to ensure an airtight seal. Make sure the inner chamber is in place.",
            "Modify one of the middle foam layers to accommodate the electrical system components, ensuring they do not protrude above the trimmed layer.",
            "Inoculate Petrifilms using sterile water for a control and water from a likely contaminated source, following 3M's instructions for inoculation and marking each film with the sample name.",
            "Place a cardboard divider on top of the heating pad holder and place your petrifilms on top of the cardboard.",
            "Seal the incubator by closing the inner chamber, adding remaining foam layers, ensuring a completely sealed lid. Set a timer for 48 hours, maintaining a temperature of 37\u00b11\u00b0C.",
            "Test the incubator and after incubation, remove the Petrifilms and analyze the results. Make sure that the results correlate with the control and the contaminated sample."
        ]
